context: The word 'tüübid' is the plural form of the Estonian noun 'tüüp', which means 'type' or 'kind'. In English, this would correspond to words like 'types', 'kinds', or 'sorts'. It's used when referring to multiple categories or classifications of things. For example, in the sentence 'Mul on head tüübid,' it could mean 'I have good types/kinds.'
